<inglise> Commission Regulation (EC) No 1469/94 of 27 June 1994 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1164/89 laying down detailed rules concerning the aid for fibre flax and hemp </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1469/94, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1164/89, milles s&auml;testatakse kiulina ja kanepi toetust k&auml;sitlevad &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad 27. juuni 1994 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1380/70 of 29 June 1970 on the common organization of the market in flax and hemp (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1557/93 (2), and in particular Article 4 (5) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 lina- ja kanepituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1557/93, (2) eriti selle artikli 4 l&otilde;iget 5, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 4 (a) of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1164/89 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2095/93 (4), lays down, inter alia, that the aid is to be granted only in respect of areas harvested, on condition that normal cultivation work has been carried out; whereas, if the aid scheme is to operate properly, a definition should be given of what is meant by harvest, on the one hand, and on the other only those cultivation practices which seek to valorize almost the whole of the product cultivated should be accepted; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1164/89 (3) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2095/93) (4) artikli 4 punktis a s&auml;testatakse muu hulgas toetuse andmine ainult koristatud alade puhul, kui neid on haritud tavap&auml;rasel viisil; toetuskava n&otilde;uetekohase toimimise tagamiseks tuleks &uuml;helt poolt m&auml;&auml;ratleda koristuse m&otilde;iste ja teiselt poolt tunnistada ainult neid viljelusviise, mis p&uuml;&uuml;avad v&auml;&auml;rtustada peaaegu kogu kasvatatud toodet; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas pursuant to the third subparagraph of Article 4 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1308/70, the amount of aid for flax is to be varied by applying coefficients to be fixed on the one hand for retted, non-deseeded flax and, on the other, for flax other than retted, non-deseeded flax; whereas these two cultivation methods must be distinguishable; whereas this can be achieved by requiring the applicant to state in his aid application which method of cultivation he has chosen; whereas, in order to avoid the risk of fraudulent applications, the checking of such applications should be facilitated, and penalties should be imposed on operators who have submitted irregular aid applications; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 artikli 4 l&otilde;ike 2 kolmanda l&otilde;igu kohaselt peavad lina toetuse m&auml;&auml;rad olema erinevad, kohaldades koefitsiente, mis m&auml;&auml;ratakse nii leotatud kupardamata linale kui ka leotamata kupardamata linale; nimetatud kaks viljelusviisi peavad olema eristatavad; seda v&otilde;ib saavutada n&otilde;udmisega, et taotleja deklareeriks valitud viljelusviisi oma toetusetaotluses; ebaausate taotluste riski v&auml;ltimiseks tuleks taotluste kontrolli lihtsustada ja kehtestada sanktsioonid tootjate suhtes, kes on esitanud n&otilde;udeid eiravad taotlused; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Annex A to Regulation (EEC) No 1164/89 contains a list of varieties of flax grown mainly for fibre so that those varieties can be distinguished from non-fibre varieties; whereas, as a result of the use of new flax varieties grown mainly for fibre, the said Annex should be supplemented; whereas, moreover, in order to prevent the use of varieties which now appear only in the common catalogue of agricultural species, provision should be made for such varieties to be deleted from Annex A with effect from future sowings; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1164/89 A lisa sisaldab peamiselt kiu saamiseks kasvatatava lina sortide loetelu, et neid sorte saaks eristada muul otstarbel kui kiu saamiseks kasvatatava lina sortidest; peamiselt kiu saamiseks kasvatatava lina uute sortide kasutuselev&otilde;tmise t&otilde;ttu tuleks nimetatud lisa t&auml;iendada; lisaks sellele tuleks p&otilde;llumajanduskultuuride &uuml;ldisest kataloogist v&auml;lja j&auml;etud sortide kasutamise v&auml;ltimiseks s&auml;testada selliste sortide v&auml;ljaj&auml;tmine A lisast uutest k&uuml;lvidest alates; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the Management Committee for Flax and Hemp, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las lina- ja kanepituru korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 1164/89 is hereby amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1164/89 j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The following subparagraph is added to Article 4 (a): </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 4 punktile a lisatakse j&auml;rgmine l&otilde;ik: </eesti>
<inglise> 'To be considered as having been harvested, areas must have undergone an operation: </inglise>
<eesti> "et kasvualasid saaks lugeda koristatuks, peavad seal vajalikud t&ouml;&ouml;d olema: </eesti>
<inglise> - carried out after seed formation, </inglise>
<eesti> - tehtud p&auml;rast seemnete moodustumist, </eesti>
<inglise> - aimed at terminating the growing cycle of the plant, and </inglise>
<eesti> - suunatud taime kasvuts&uuml;kli l&otilde;petamisele ja </eesti>
<inglise> - carried out with the aim of valorizing the stalk, with or without seed. </inglise>
<eesti> - tehtud kas seemnetega v&otilde;i seemneteta varre v&auml;&auml;rtustamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> The valorization referred to in the third indent shall be considered as having been desired if the plant has been pulled up or if it has been cut by a cutter bar operating, in the case of flax and hemp, at a maximum height of 10 cm and 20 cm respectively from the ground. </inglise>
<eesti> Kolmandas taandes nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtustamist peetakse soovitavaks, kui taim on kitkutud v&otilde;i niidetud niiduagregaadiga, mis lina ja kanepi puhul t&ouml;&ouml;tab maapinnast k&otilde;ige enam vastavalt 10 cm ja 20 cm k&otilde;rgusel. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards the requirement as to the height of the cutter bar: </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses niiduagregaadi k&otilde;rguse n&otilde;udega: </eesti>
<inglise> - areas must be kept in a state allowing it to be verified during the 20 days following the date of submission of the aid application or the request for checks; by way of derogation from this provision, Member States shall, in respect of the 1994/95 marketing year, take the necessary measures to verify that this requirement is satisfied as soon as harvesting starts, </inglise>
<eesti> - tuleb kasvualad hoida seisukorras, mis v&otilde;imaldab kontrolli 20 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast toetuse- v&otilde;i kontrollitaotluse esitamise kuup&auml;eva; erandina sellest s&auml;ttest v&otilde;tavad liikmesriigid 1994/95. turustusaasta puhul vajalikke meetmeid, et kontrollida nimetatud n&otilde;ude t&auml;itmist niipea kui koristus algab, </eesti>
<inglise> - Member States may take special harvest conditions into account. </inglise>
<eesti> - liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad arvesse v&otilde;tta koristuse eritingimusi." </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 (2) is replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 8 l&otilde;ige 2 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> '2. </inglise>
<eesti> "2. </eesti>
<inglise> Aid applications shall contain: </inglise>
<eesti> Toetusetaotlustele tuleb m&auml;rkida: </eesti>
<inglise> - the surname, first name(s) and address of the applicant, </inglise>
<eesti> - taotleja perekonnanimi, eesnimi/eesnimed ja aadress, </eesti>
<inglise> - a declaration in hectares and ares of the areas harvested, and the cadastral register number of those areas, or a reference recognized as equivalent by the body responsible for checking the areas, stating, in the case of flax, the part relating to retted, non-deseeded flax and the part relating to flax other than retted, non-deseeded flax, and specifying if it has been pulled up and/or deseeded, </inglise>
<eesti> - deklaratsioon koristuspinna kohta hektarites ja aarides ning k&otilde;nealuste alade katastritunnus v&otilde;i alade kontrollimise eest vastutava asutuse poolt tunnustatud v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rne m&auml;rge; lina puhul deklareeritakse leotatud kupardamata lina ja leotamata kupardamata lina ning t&auml;psustatakse, kas lina on kitkutud ja/v&otilde;i kupardatud, </eesti>
<inglise> - details of the place where the product concerned is stored and, where appropriate, in the case of seed, separate details, or, if it has been sold and delivered, the name, first name(s) and address of the purchaser. </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;ksikasjad asjaomase saaduse ladustamiskoha kohta ja vajaduse korral seemnete puhul eraldi &uuml;ksikasjad v&otilde;i juhul, kui see on m&uuml;&uuml;dud ja tarnitud, ostja nimi, eesnimi/eesnimed ja aadress." </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
