<inglise> Article 8 (5) is replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 8 l&otilde;ige 5 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> '5. </inglise>
<eesti> "5. </eesti>
<inglise> If the checks provided for in Article 5 of Regulation (EEC) No 619/71 show: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71 artiklis 5 etten&auml;htud kontrollimiste k&auml;igus ilmneb, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) that for hemp and for flax, without distinction between the part under retted non-deseeded flax and the part under flax other than retted, non-deseeded flax, the area in respect of which the aid is applied for differs from that ascertained during checks, the amount of the aid shall be calculated on the basis of the following area: </inglise>
<eesti> a) kanepi ja lina puhul (leotatud kupardamata ning leotamata kupardamata lina osa eristamata) erineb ala, millele toetust taotletakse, kontrollimisel tuvastatud alast, arvutatakse toetuse summa ala p&otilde;hjal j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> - where the area ascertained is greater than that shown in the aid application, the area ascertained shall be used, </inglise>
<eesti> - kui tuvastatud ala on suurem kui toetusetaotluses n&auml;idatud, v&otilde;etakse arvesse tuvastatud ala, </eesti>
<inglise> - where the area ascertained is less than that shown in the aid application, the area to be used shall be that ascertained minus the difference between the two areas. </inglise>
<eesti> - kui tuvastatud ala on v&auml;iksem kui toetusetaotluses n&auml;idatud, v&otilde;etakse arvesse tuvastatud ala, mida on v&auml;hendatud tuvastatud ja toetusetaotluses n&auml;idatud alade erinevuse v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise> However, the aid application shall be rejected if the difference is more than 25 % of the ascertained area or if, for the person making the declaration in question, the areas indicated in his declarations or applications have been reduced during the same marketing year or the preceding one in accordance with Article 7 or with this paragraph. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui erinevus on suurem kui 25% tuvastatud alast v&otilde;i kui k&otilde;nealuse taotleja deklaratsioonides v&otilde;i avaldustes n&auml;idatud alasid on samal v&otilde;i eelmisel turustusaastal vastavalt artiklile 7 v&otilde;i k&auml;esolevale l&otilde;ikele v&auml;hendatud, l&uuml;katakse toetusetaotlus tagasi. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the second indent applies to areas under flax, the reduction shall in the first place apply to areas under flax other than retted, non-deseeded flax. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui lina kasvualade suhtes kohaldatakse teist taanet, kehtib v&auml;hendamine eelk&otilde;ige leotamata kupardamata lina kasvualade puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> (b) that an area under retted, non-deseeded flax has been declared in the aid application as an area under flax other than retted, non-deseeded flax, the total amount of the aid to be granted shall, having taken account, where appropriate, of the second indent of (a), be reduced, in respect of each hectare or part of a hectare of retted, non-deseeded flax declared as flax other than retted, non-deseeded flax, by an amount equal to 15 % of the aid applicable to flax other than retted, non-deseeded flax. </inglise>
<eesti> b) leotatud kupardamata lina kasvuala on toetusetaotluses deklareeritud leotamata kupardatud lina kasvualana, v&auml;hendatakse vajaduse korral punkti a teist taanet arvesse v&otilde;ttes antava toetuse kogum&auml;&auml;ra leotamata kupardamata lina kasvualana deklareeritud leotatud kupardamata lina kasvuala iga hektari v&otilde;i hektariosa puhul 15% leotamata kupardatud lina puhul kohaldatava toetuse m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the inaccurate declarations referred to in (a) and (b) are considered justified by the Member State concerned, no penalty shall be applied. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui asjaomane liikmesriik peab punktides a ja b nimetatud ebat&auml;pseid deklaratsioone &otilde;igustatuks, sanktsioone ei kohaldata. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of this paragraph shall apply without prejudice to any penalties provided for under national law. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike s&auml;tete kohaldamine ei piira siseriiklikus &otilde;iguses s&auml;testatud sanktsioonide kohaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall notify the Commission of the measures taken in pursuance of this paragraph. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike alusel v&otilde;etavatest meetmetest." </eesti>
